o not match to the Date of Birth provided on the Client input file.", "classification": "Count", "type": "Num (6)"}, {"reference": "EA4-S-04", "reference_concat": "ea4s04", "type of data": "SP", "description": "CAIS Date of Birth", "clarification": "The most common date of birth found on CAIS Accounts that is different to the Date of Birth provided on the Client input file.", "classification": "DDMMYY", "type": "Num (1)"}, {"reference": "EA4-S-05", "reference_concat": "ea4s05", "type of data": "SP", "description": "A count of the number of different Date Of Births that are found on Previous Search Records that are not the same as the input", "clarification": "A count of the number of different date of births found on Previous Search Records that does not match to the Date of Birth provided on the Client input file.", "classification": "Count", "type": "Num (6)"}, {"reference": "EA4-S-06", "reference_concat": "ea4s06", "type of data": "SP", "description": "Previous Search Records Date of Birth", "clarification": "The most common date of birth found on previous Search Records that is different to the Date of Birth provided on the Client input file.", "classification": "DDMMYY", "type": "Char (6)"}, {"reference": "EA4-S-07", "reference_concat": "ea4s07", "type of data": "SP", "description": "A count of the number of different Date Of Births that are found on the Electoral Roll, Previous Search Records and CAIS that are not the same as the input", "clarification": "A count of the number of different Date Of Births found on the Electoral Roll, Previous Search Records and CAIS accounts that doe not match to the Date of Birth provided on the Client input file.", "classification": "Count", "type": "Num (1)"}, {"reference": "EA4-S-08", "reference_concat": "ea4s08", "type of data": "SP", "description": "Previous Search Records and CAIS Accounts Date of Birth", "clarification": "The most common date of birth found on previous Search Records and CAIS Accounts that is different to the Date of Birth provided on the Client input file.", "classification": "DDMMYY", "type": "Char (6)"}, {"reference": "ND-SP-CII,ND-SPA-CII", "reference_concat": "ndspcii,ndspacii", "type of data": "SP,SPA", "description": "Consumer Indebtedness Index", "clarification": "Consumer Indebtedness Index (CII) is set within Strategy Manager .Please refer to the relevant CII user guides for information on ranges and special values as these change from generation to generation", "classification": "Number", "type": "Num (2)"}, {"reference": "ND-FCS-01,ND-FCS-02", "reference_concat": "ndfcs01,ndfcs02", "type of data": "SP,SPA", "description": "FCS CUG Flag", "clarification": "Federation of Communication Services (FCS). Set to worst FCS value (Live, Banned or Disconnected) returned on all FCS CAIS accounts.", "classification": "FCS CUG", "type": "Num (2)"}, {"reference": "SUS-IND", "reference_concat": "susind", "type of data": null, "description": "Suspicious Activity Indicator", "clarification": "Contains \u00e2\u20ac\u0153Y\u00e2\u20ac or \u00e2\u20ac\u0153N\u00e2\u20ac depending on whether the address of the applicant has been determined to be suspicious (i.e. is present on the suspicious activity file)", "classification": "Yes/No", "type": "Char(1)"}, {"reference": "ND-DIR-SP", "reference_concat": "nddirsp", "type of data": "SP", "description": "Directors Info found (SP)", "clarification": "Set to \u00e2\u20ac\u02dcY\u00e2\u20ac\u2122 if any H01 segments with a bureau ref category of \u00e2\u20ac\u02dc1\u00e2\u20ac\u2122 are found, set to \u00e2\u20ac\u02dcN\u00e2\u20ac\u2122 otherwise. Will be set even if the block is No Trace.This reference is not returned through the Retro.", "classification": "Yes/No", "type": "Char(1)"}, {"reference": "ND-DIR-SPA", "reference_concat": "nddirspa", "type of data": "SPA", "description": "Directors Info found (SPA)", "clarification": "Set to \u00e2\u20ac\u02dcY\u00e2\u20ac\u2122 if any H01 segments with a bureau ref category of \u00e2\u20ac\u02dc2\u00e2\u20ac\u2122 are found, set to \u00e2\u20ac\u02dcN\u00e2\u20ac\u2122 otherwise. Will be set even if the block is No Trace. This reference is not returned through the Retro.", "classification": "Yes/No", "type": "Char(1)"}, {"reference": "ND-ICH", "reference_concat": "ndich", "type of data": "SP", "description": "Impaired Credit History Indicator", "clarification": "The ICH references are optional and need to be requested by the client. If the client is not configured for ICH, then this will be set to \u00e2\u20ac\u02dcZ\u00e2\u20ac\u2122. Set to \u00e2\u20ac\u02dcY\u00e2\u20ac\u2122 if any other ICH References are set. Otherwise set to \u00e2\u20ac\u02dcN\u00e2\u20ac\u2122.", "classification": "Character", "type": "Char (1)"}, {"reference": "ND-G-12", "reference_concat": "ndg12", "type of data": null, "description": "Percentage of Households with a Credit Limit greater than \u00c2\u00a310,000", "clarification": "Taken directly from the Geo-Delphi File. Matched by Postcode", "classification": "Geo-Delphi Percentage", "type": "Num (5)"}, {"reference": "ND-SEC-ARR", "reference_concat": "ndsecarr", "type of data": "SP", "description": "ICH \u00e2\u20ac\u201c Secured Arrears", "clarification": "The ICH references are optional and need to be requested by the client. If the client is not configured for ICH, then this will be set to \u00e2\u20ac\u02dcZ\u00e2\u20ac\u2122. Set to \u00e2\u20ac\u02dcA\u00e2\u20ac\u2122 if at any point in the last 2 years the arrears status reached three or more monthly payments (regardless of balance), for a previous (or current) mortgage or other secured loan. Otherwise set to \u00e2\u20ac\u02dcN\u00e2\u20ac\u2122.", "classification": "Character", "type": "Char (1)"}, {"reference": "ND-UNSEC-ARR", "reference_concat": "ndunsecarr", "type of data": "SP", "description": "ICH \u00e2\u20ac\u201c Unsecured Arrears", "clarification": "The ICH references are optional and need to be requested by the client. If the client is not configured for ICH, then this will be set to \u00e2\u20ac\u02dcZ\u00e2\u20ac\u2122. Set to \u00e2\u20ac\u02dcA\u00e2\u20ac\u2122 if at any point in the last 2 years the arrears status reached three or more monthly payments (regardless of balance), for a previous (or current) unsecured loan. Note that this only applies to Loans \u00e2\u20ac\u201c Credit Cards, Mail Order, Telcos etc are not included.Otherwise set to \u00e2\u20ac\u02dcN\u00e2\u20ac\u2122.", "classification": "Character", "type": "Char (1)"}, {"reference": "ND-CCJ", "reference_concat": "ndccj", "type of data": "SP", "description": "ICH \u00e2\u20ac\u201c County Court Judgements", "clarification": "The ICH references are optional and need to be requested by the client. If the client is not configured for ICH, then this will be set to -9999.if there have been one or more County Court Judgments with a total value greater than \u00c2\u00a3500, within the last three years, then this is set to the total value, banded into a code representing \u00c2\u00a350 intervals.Otherwise set to zero if no CCJ or set to 1 if low value of CCJ.CCJ Definition", "classification": "Value > \u00c2\u00a3500(\u00c2\u00a350 intervals)", "type": "Num (4)"}, {"reference": "ND-IVA", "reference_concat": "ndiva", "type of data": "SP", "description": "ICH \u00e2\u20ac\u201c Individual Voluntary Arrangement", "clarification": "The ICH references are optional and need to be requested by the client. If the client is not configured for ICH, then this will be set to \u00e2\u20ac\u02dcZ\u00e2\u20ac\u2122.Set to \u00e2\u20ac\u02dcV\u00e2\u20ac\u2122 if there has been an active Individual Voluntary Arrangement at any time within the last 3 years.Otherwise set to \u00e2\u20ac\u02dcN\u00e2\u20ac\u2122.IVA Definition", "classification": "Character", "type": "Char (1)"}, {"reference": "ND-Bankrupt", "reference_concat": "ndbankrupt", "type of data": "SP", "description": "ICH \u00e2\u20ac\u201c Bankruptcy", "clarification": "The ICH references are optional and need to be requested by the client. If the client is not configured for ICH, then this will be set to \u00e2\u20ac\u02dcZ\u00e2\u20ac\u2122.Set to \u00e2\u20ac\u02dcB\u00e2\u20ac\u2122 if there has been a Bankruptcy Order or Scottish Sequestration in force at any time within the last 3 years.Otherwise set to \u00e2\u20ac\u02dcN\u00e2\u20ac\u2122.Bankruptcy Definition(Excludes Administration Order Revoked or Varied)", "classification": "Character", "type": "Char (1)"}]
